				<article> 
					<h2 id="atomic">The Problem with Non-White People</h2> 
					<p class="post-meta"> 
						Published on November 15, 2023  

						<img class="img3" src="/public/images/MJ and Gilbert.jpeg" alt="VO Gear">
					</p> 
					<p> 
						Today I reminisced about that time when I was part of a
						"focus group" providing feedback on "Rainbow" initiatives 
						to our corporate overlords who wanted to improve diversity
						and inclusiveness across the company. A small group of us were 
						set up with a polyphone in the Boardroom, dialled in on speakerphone
						with a group in Head Office. In terms of doing a "diversity and inclusiveness" survey via
						email, we were trying to convince them that such an approach wouldn't 
						yield much result because we had so many non-white staff. They 
						just couldn't see the issue, refused to see it. Why couldn't they 
						email out an online survey to everyone? Geez - we eye-rolled hard - BECAUSE 
						SO MANY OF OUR STAFF ARE NON-WHITE; the problem is obvious! Silence.
						Why did the silence seem - awkward?? Could we repeat the problem again,
						just to be clear. Sure - our staff work on a factory floor and the majority
						are non-wired!<br>  
						They're what?<br>
						NON-WIRED - they don't have access to computers and don't have an email!<br>
						You can imagine the relief was palpable when they realised we'd actually been saying
						"NON-WIRED" that whole time. 
											
		
						
